{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Chronicles 22 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:1",
      "text": "Now these are the priests and the Levites that went up with Zorobabel the son of Salathiel and Jesus: Saraia, Jeremia, Esdra,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:2",
      "text": "Amaria, Maluch,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:3",
      "text": "Sechenia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:4",
      "text": "And he did that which was evil in the sight of the Lord as the house of Achaab had done: for they were his counsellors after the death of his father to his destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:5",
      "text": "And he walked in their counsels, and he went with Joram son of Achaab king of Israel to war against Azael king of Syria to Ramoth Galaad: and the archers smote Joram.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:6",
      "text": "And Joram returned to Jezrael to be healed of the wounds wherewith the Syrians smote him in Ramoth, when he fought against Azael king of Syria. And Ochozias son of Joram, king of Juda, went down to see Joram the son of Achaab at Jezrael because he was sick.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:7",
      "text": "These were the chiefs of the priests, and their brethren in the days of Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:8",
      "text": "And the Levites were, Jesus, Banui, Cadmiel, Sarabia, Jodae, Matthania: he was over the bands, and his brethren",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:9",
      "text": "were appointed to the daily courses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:10",
      "text": "And Jesus begot Joakim, and Joakim begot Eliasib, and Eliasib begot Jodae,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:11",
      "text": "and Jodae begot Jonathan, and Jonathan begot Jadu.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:12",
      "text": "And in the days of Joakim, his brethren the priests and the heads of families were, belonging to Saraia, Amaria; to Jeremia, Anania;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:13",
      "text": "to Esdra, Mesulam; to Amaria, Joanan;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:14",
      "text": "to Amaluch, Jonathan; to Sechenia, Joseph;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:15",
      "text": "to Are, Mannas; to Marioth, Elcaï;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:16",
      "text": "to Adadai, Zacharia; to Ganathoth, Mesolam;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:17",
      "text": "to Abia, Zechri; to Miamin, Maadai; to Pheleti, one;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:18",
      "text": "to Balgas, Samue; to Semia, Jonathan;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:19",
      "text": "to Joarib, Matthanai; to Edio, Ozi;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:20",
      "text": "to Salai, Callai; to Amec, Abed;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:21",
      "text": "to Elkia, Asabias; to Jedeiu, Nathanael.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:22",
      "text": "The Levites in the days of Eliasib, Joada, and Joa, and Joanan, and Idua, were recorded heads of families: also the priests, in the reign of Darius the Persian.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:23",
      "text": "And the sons of Levi, heads of families, were written in the book of the chronicles, even to the days of Joanan son of Elisue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:24",
      "text": "And the heads of the Levites were Asabia, and Sarabia, and Jesu: and the sons of Cadmiel, and their brethren over against them, were to sing hymns of praise, according to the commandment of David the man of God, course by course.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:25",
      "text": "When I gathered the porters,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:26",
      "text": "it was in the days of Joakim son of Jesus, son of Josedec, and in the days of Neemia: and Esdras the priest was scribe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:27",
      "text": "And at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought the Levites in their places, to bring them to Jerusalem, to keep a feast of dedication and gladness with thanksgiving, and they sounded cymbals with songs, and had psalteries and harps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:28",
      "text": "And the sons of the singers were assembled both from the neighbourhood round about to Jerusalem, and from the villages,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:29",
      "text": "and from the country: for the singers built themselves villages by Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:30",
      "text": "And the priests and the Levites purified themselves, and they purified the people, and the porters, and the wall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:31",
      "text": "And they brought up the princes of Juda on the wall, and they appointed two great companies for thanksgiving, and they passed on the right hand on the wall of the dung-gate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:32",
      "text": "And after them went Osaia, and half the princes of Juda,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:33",
      "text": "and Azarias, and Esdras, and Mesollam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.34",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:34",
      "text": "and Juda, and Benjamin, and Samaias and Jeremia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.35",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:35",
      "text": "And some of the sons of the priests with trumpets, Zacharias son of Jonathan, son of Samaias, son of Matthania, son of Michaia, son of Zacchur, son of Asaph:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:36",
      "text": "and his brethren, Samaia, and Oziel, Gelol, Jama, Aia, Nathanael, and Juda, Anani, to praise with the hymns of David the man of God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.37",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:37",
      "text": "and Esdras the scribe was before them, at the gate, to praise before them, and they went up by the steps of the city of David, in the ascent of the wall, above the house of David, even to the water-gate",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.39",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:39",
      "text": "of Ephraim, and to the fish-gate, and by the tower of Anameel, and as far as the sheep-gate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.42",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:42",
      "text": "And the singers were heard, and were numbered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.43",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:43",
      "text": "And in that day they offered great sacrifices, and rejoiced; for God had made them very joyful: and their wives and their children rejoiced: and the joy in Jerusalem was heard from afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.44",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:44",
      "text": "And in that day they appointed men over the treasuries, for the treasures, the first-fruits, and the tithes, and for the chiefs of the cities who were assembled among them, to furnish portions for the priests and Levites: for there was joy in Juda over the priests and over the Levites that waited.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.45",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:45",
      "text": "And they kept the charges of their God, and the charges of the purification, and ordered the singers and the porters, according to the commandments of David and his son Solomon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.46",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:46",
      "text": "For in the days of David Asaph was originally first of the singers, and they sang hymns and praise to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.22.47",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 22:47",
      "text": "And all Israel in the days of Zorobabel, and in the days of Neemias, gave the portions of the singers and the porters, a daily rate: and consecrated them to the Levites: and the Levites consecrated them to the sons of Aaron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
